    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend rules for UK travel for vaccinated travellers to unvaccinated travellers",
        "additional_details": "Data has shown that both vaccinated and unvaccinated people can contract and spread covid19. Also the efficacy of the vaccination reduces over time. Therefore, we believe there is no justification for treating vaccinated and unvaccinated travellers differently, requiring the unvaccinated to take expensive PRC tests and isolate for 10 days. Unvaccinated travellers are treated as 2nd class citizens because of their choices over their own body.",
        "background": "From 4th October 2021 and onwards, vaccinated and unvaccinated travellers are treated differently. Unvaccinated travellers are required to take expensive PRC tests and isolate for 10 days. The same rules should apply to vaccinated and unvaccinated travellers.",
